   <abstract>The J.J. Craig Company founded the Candoro Marble Works in South Knoxville in 1914. This business finished marble blocks taken from quarries in Knox, Blount, and Loudon counties in addition to marble imported from around the world. At its peak, it employed about 140 people.</abstract>
